author: THE NEWS HERALD sports@pcnh.com
title: Mosley rolls by Blountstown 3-0
text: Posted Oct. 15, 2015 at 10:07 PM Updated at 10:08 PM LYNN HAVEN — The Dolphins capped off their regular season with a three-set win over Blountstown, taking the match 25-14, 25-7, 25-14 to improve to 18-7. Kenley Adams led the way with 19 assists, 11 kills, seven digs, seven service points, and a block, while T’ara Ceasar added 11 kills, 12 service points, eight digs, three blocks, and two aces. Kiana Yangson had 11 digs, 10 service points, two aces, and four assists, with Laney Haynes contributing five kills and two blocks, Savannah Gibbs 14 assists and six service points, and Savannah Stanton 10 service points, four kills, and two a ces. Lauren Mask also had four kills and two blocks, with Josie Williams adding three kills and two blocks. Camryn May had three kills. Mosley will next compete in the District 1-5A tournament at ArnoldHigh School, opening Tuesday against Rutherford. By THE NEWS HERALD
